# Extra harness-hash pin patterns for bobs-big-brain-umbrella.
#
# This repo is docs + shell + python — it has no test suite, no coverage config,
# and no architecture-rule config, so NONE of audit-harness's default canonical
# patterns match here and a bare `init` pins zero files. A manifest pinning
# nothing still reports "harness-hash: OK", which is a hollow gate: it verifies
# that nothing changed about nothing.
#
# What this repo DOES have is one real enforcement artifact — the docs-honesty
# linter. It encodes the ISEDC 009-AT-DECR D1 / CISO binding that a public claim
# may never assert tamper-proof / immutable / non-repudiation / blockchain (the
# trust model is tamper-EVIDENT). Quietly relaxing that script's word list or
# its negation handling would weaken a governance gate while leaving CI green —
# exactly the escape class harness-hash exists to detect.
#
# Deliberately NOT pinned:
#   repos.yml  — it is a topology manifest, not an enforcement gate. Its observed
#                failure mode is going STALE (nobody edited it when two repos were
#                renamed), and a content hash cannot detect an edit that never
#                happened. Pinning it would add re-init ceremony to every
#                legitimate topology change while catching nothing real.
#   bin/gsb    — an operator convenience tool; it enforces no policy.
#
# After any REVIEWED edit to a pinned file, re-pin with:
#   ./scripts/audit-harness init
scripts/lint-forbidden-words.sh
